get off 1) If someone who has broken a law or rule gets off, they are not punished, or are given only a very small punishment. [V with ] He is likely to get off with a small fine. 2) If you get off, you leave a place because it is time to leave. [V ] At eight I said: I'm getting off now. 3) If you tell someone to get off a piece of land or a property, you are telling them to leave, because they have no right to be there and you do not want them there. [V ] I told you: get off the farm. 4) You can tell someone to get off when they are touching something and you do not want them to. [V ] I kept telling him to get off... 5) If you get off to sleep, you succeed in falling asleep. [BRIT]